HEADWORD: Mactra
<hw>Mac"tra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
kneading trough, fr. <?/ to knead.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
marine bivalve shell of the genus <gen>Mactra</gen>, and allied genera.
Many species are known. Some of them are used as food, as <spn>Mactra
stultorum</spn>, of Europe. See <cref>Surf clam</cref>, under
<er>Surf</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

